properties.Name: EquifaxBusinessCreditIndustryGroupReport
properties.Description:
SUMMARY - Open Non-Financial Accounts by Industry Group
This table summarizes open non-financial accounts, by credit grantor industry, with a date reported within 24 months of inquiry.

SUMMARY - Closed Non-Financial Accounts by Industry Group
This table summarizes closed non-financial accounts, by credit grantor industry, with a closed date within 24 months of inquiry.

Columns.Name: EquifaxIndustryGroupId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of an Equifax Industry Group.

Columns.Name: EfxId
Columns.Description: The EFX IDâ„¢ is a unique and persistent nine-digit number that identifies and tracks the business unit with which you have the credit relationship;

Columns.Name: ProfileTimestamp
Columns.Description:
Provides the timestamp when the inquiry was made as recorded
by Equifax (Eastern Time).

Columns.Name: NumberOfAccounts
Columns.Description: Count of open accounts by industry group.

Columns.Name: MostSevereStatusComment
Columns.Description:
Returns the most severe current status experienced by one of the credit grantors in this industry group.

EX:
- Current
- Slow up to 3

Columns.Name: HighestBalanceAmount
Columns.Description: The single highest credit extended or past due from one of the credit grantors for that industry group.

Columns.Name: HighestTotalPastDueAmount
Columns.Description: The single highest total past due as reported by one of the credit grantors for that industry group.

Columns.Name: BalanceAmount
Columns.Description: Sum of all the total reported balances including any past due amount.

Columns.Name: PastDueAmount
Columns.Description: Sum of all past due amounts (excluding charge-offs).

Columns.Name: SlowUpTo30Amount
Columns.Description: The amount of that aging category's dollars compared to total past due up to 30 days.

Columns.Name: SlowUpTo30Percentage
Columns.Description: The percentage of that aging category's dollars compared to total past due up to 30 days.

Columns.Name: SlowUpTo60Amount
Columns.Description: The amount of that aging category's dollars compared to total past due up to 60 days.

Columns.Name: SlowUpTo60Percentage
Columns.Description: The percentage of that aging category's dollars compared to total past due up to 60 days.

Columns.Name: SlowUpTo90Amount
Columns.Description: The amount of that aging category's dollars compared to total past due up to 90 days.

Columns.Name: SlowUpTo90Percentage
Columns.Description: The percentage of that aging category's dollars compared to total past due up to 90 days.

Columns.Name: SlowUpTo120Amount
Columns.Description: The amount of that aging category's dollars compared to total past due up to 120 days.

Columns.Name: SlowUpTo120Percentage
Columns.Description: The percentage of that aging category's dollars compared to total past due up to 120 days.

Columns.Name: SlowUp121PlusAmount
Columns.Description: The amount of that aging category's dollars compared to total past due exceeding 120 days.

Columns.Name: SlowUp120PlusPercentage
Columns.Description: The percentage of that aging category's dollars compared to total past due exceeding 120 days.

Columns.Name: SingleHighestCreditExtendedAmount
Columns.Description: The highest credit amount that was extended for all accounts closed.

Columns.Name: TotalHighCreditAmount
Columns.Description: Total highest credit or balance extended for all accounts closed in current standing ($0 balance).

Columns.Name: NumberOfAccountsClosedInGoodStanding
Columns.Description: Number of accounts closed with a $0 balance.

Columns.Name: MostRecentDateClosedInCurrentStanding
Columns.Description: The most recent date closed for all accounts closed in current standing.

Columns.Name: NumberOfAccountsClosedInDelinquentStatus
Columns.Description: Number of all accounts closed with a delinquent status.

Columns.Name: MostRecentDateClosedInDelinquentStatus
Columns.Description: The most recent closed date for all accounts closed with a delinquent status.

Columns.Name: BalanceAtClosedDateAmount
Columns.Description: Total outstanding balances for all accounts closed with a delinquent status.

Columns.Name: NumberOfAccountsClosedInChargeOffStatus
Columns.Description: Number of accounts charged-off.

Columns.Name: MostRecentDateClosedInChargeOffStatus
Columns.Description: The most recent date closed for all accounts closed with a charged-off status.

Columns.Name: BalanceAtChargeOffDate
Columns.Description: Reported balances of all charged-off accounts at the date closed. Balance may not equal charged-off amount in the Report Highlights due to interest, penalties, and late fees which may have been reported after the closed date.

Columns.Name: GrandTotalAmount
Columns.Description: Number of closed non-financial accounts by status at closed date; sums total balance in delinquent and charged-off status at date closed.
